what is mongodb?
A: mongodb is non-sql database. It is stores data in form of json-format(or) document-form like key-value pair.
each of these documents consisting of key/value attributes.
mongodb has set number of documents is called collections.

          or

mongodb is a collection of documents.
mongodb stores data in form of documents(json format like key-value pair).

